winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Riesling, and Sauvignon Blanc are great choices for Shrimp. These crisp white wines work well with shrimp prepared in a variety of ways, whether grilled, fried, or in garlic sauce. The Maso Canali Pinot Grigio with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 15 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Maso Canali Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: The Maso Canali Pinot Grigio displays a brilliant pale golden color indicative of its crisp, citrus aromas and floral notes. This wine is well-balanced and full-flavored with hints of nectarine. Pair it with seafood and light poultry for a delightful meal.
